'''''Adam and Steve''''' is a [[2005 in film|2005]] [[film]], directed by [[Craig Chester]]. It deals with the lives of two [[homosexuality|gay]] men. It got its [[United Kingdom|UK]] premier on [[November 19]] at the [[Cardiff Screen Festival]]

This is a play on the unclever line used by many anti-gay/anti-gay marriage "activists," who often say "it's Adam and ''Eve'', not Adam and St''eve''."

